These are setup instructions for running on macOS Big Sur. I don't have any extra machines to test a new installation with, so YMMV.
These are also very rudimentary installation instructions. No warranties or guarantees here, etc. etc. 

——————— Install————————

Download or clone the repository. In a Terminal window, change to type the directory you’d like to the use for the files. Type: 
git clone https://github.com/jim-buell/AINN.git

Change to the directory of the repository. Type:
cd AINN

Install a virtual environment. Type:
python3 -m venv venv

Activate the virtual environment. Type:
source venv/bin/activate

Install required packages into your virtual environment using the following command:
pip3 install -r requirements.txt

Install language processing data from nltk with the following command:
python3 -m nltk.downloader popular

To run the program, type:
python main.py
